London m. Henry Collier
mij last to you was on the 6 curtt. senceerecd yd of 24 pass, as for m wa
bustijnes I referre all till I see you, as for J. the sentence exciution es upon
sid goods, of whuch wee finde non, & is also upon his paison, butt de bides hi
self, so more of that also, when you be here, as for yd 3 bills of Trowne to
impon for mee t0 pay them att present, haveing as I told you so first a summe
to pay, so you please to provide for them, haveing all ready don what lyes in my
power, & shall accept yd bill of Â£52:11:4 flenth, desiring, you fusther to draw no
more, for I should not be able to comply to yd. desire, being already in dis bours
for consideable some, & for drawing & redrawing as wee now do, stands noway
with mj conveniency nor credit which was the onely reason that I boock in yd bill
not beeng willing itt should go to any other hand, so do wonder how you woule
guith other wise, & understand itt an accomodaton, where as I mae nomenton
of any such word, though I lonceire itt was for boath a creditt
a9 meijs
Brussel m. Joseph Sabbarton
accrding to what I desired yeasterday do exspect without any faile some laces
for amunday morning, I could wish anight rayle of an ill broad, for m. Vivian
is still hen, & I am without any laces, & yett he wants some before ths deparine
which I supose will be atnesday or wednesday next then fores pray faile not
I have accepted, yd. bill, though you gave mee no advise, I hope I have not don
amiss there is a vere good oportunitie of shipping goods att Bruges aboaud a
vessel for london who is vere espect in the smoghis trade and recomanded to mee
for freinds - Pray note the laces as the last with an unknowne hand &
augemented the prow., I have sent yd ryssach to Arssens in bis pack

Brugge Raphael Coots
8 deser hebbe aen ul ges als mede gd, t'sedert den ul van 8 & gisteren ontf. door den
lesten mij verwonderende, te verstaen dat den mijnen van 8d. ul niet was gewoorden, die hope
dan met dien van gd. te reght sullen geraecken, waer uyt ul can verstaen als dat de 2
packettiens die ul ontf heeft H.W.N.1.2. sijn voor m. Henrij Willington, oversulckx ul
sijn ad. daer mede gelieft te volgen. Heden seijnde aen ul p bode 2 packettiens te weeten
A.V.M.M.N.4 om boort om 't selve te laeden aen boort Robert Tindale, te config aen m
abran Vivian, Item alnogh 1 packettien CWN.24 voor m. Ed. Warner, te laeden aen boort
van d. Tindale, soo gelieft ul het noodige daer voor te besorgen, & aen mij sonder uytstel
adviseeren hoe lancq d. Tindale nogh sal tardeeren eer hij vertreckt, alsoo icq nogh eenige
package gereet hebbe te maecken, waer van en naesten vrijdagh eenigh sal volgen, soo ul
adrijs tegemoet siende
